        <abstract> 
<p>Professional sheep-breeder interested in laws of inheritance reports his crosses between <hi rend="italic">Serinus hortulanus</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Dryospiza canaria</hi>. Seeks to make a new species. Crosses carried out with animals varying in their proportion of <hi rend="italic">Serinus</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Dryospiza</hi> parentage. Confirms Prosper Lucas’ law as given in <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>, ch. 9, with exception that strong individuals exhibit prepotency.</p> 
        </abstract>
