                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>
                                        </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">ditto</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">ditto</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell rend="left"/>
                                <cell rend="left">female</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>31</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">ditto</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">ditto</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
   
<p>From <hi rend="underline">every one</hi> of these crosses young were bred &amp; grew up.</p>
<p>Hereby I use the following proportions from hybrid parents on both sides: from—</p>
                 
                        <table>
                            <row>
                                <cell rend="left">I</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>61</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">Dryos.</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">Serinus</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell rend="left">II</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                    <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>29</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell rend="left">III</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>31</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell rend="left">IV</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>59</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                                <cell rend="centre">
                                    <formula>
                                        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math>
                                    </formula>
                                </cell>
                                <cell rend="left">—</cell>
                            </row>
                        </table>
                    
<p>In order under all conditions to come to the results now already attained—the formation of a new species—I have carried yet further the hybridism by pairing, and I can make use of the proportion <formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>63</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math></formula> Dryospiza, <formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>64</mn></mfrac></math></formula> Serinus, whose father is a hybrid (<formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>32</mn></mfrac></math></formula> Serinus)&amp; whose mother is Dryospiza.</p>
<p>You may use this how you like   I can vouch for the facts</p>
<p>Rud: Riemann <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Zell am See | Herzagthum Salzburg</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
